WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Shooting victim and former Arizona Congresswoman Gabrielle Giffords sought on Wednesday to rally women behind her push for stricter U.S. gun laws.

Former U.S. Rep. Gabrielle Giffords speaks to reporters during the New Eastcoast Arms Collectors Associates Arms Fair at the Saratoga Springs City Center in Saratoga Springs, New York, October 13, 2013. REUTERS/
